	<Title>
		Recipe: Chicken sliders
	</Title>
	<Abstract />
	<ServingInfo Label="Serves">
		4
	</ServingInfo>
	<DietitianTip Label="Dietitian&apos;s tip">
		&lt;p&gt;
&lt;strong&gt;Dietitian&apos;s tip:&lt;/strong&gt; These chicken &quot;sliders&quot; are a healthy change from those made with beef or pork. 
&lt;/p&gt;
	</DietitianTip>
	<Directions Label="Directions">
		&lt;p&gt;
Mix first 7 items together and let set for 1 hour. Form into 2-ounce patties. Grill or broil in oven until a minimum internal temperature of 165 F is reached. 
&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
Serve on small whole-wheat buns with lettuce and tomato.
&lt;/p&gt;
	</Directions>
	<Ingredients Label="Ingredients">
		&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;10 ounces chicken breast, ground&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 tablespoon black pepper&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 tablespoon minced garlic&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 tablespoon balsamic vinegar&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1/2 cup minced onion&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 fresh chili pepper, minced&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1 tablespoon fennel seed, crushed&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;4 whole wheat mini buns&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;4 lettuce leaves&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;4 tomato slices &lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
	</Ingredients>
